---
import BlogPostLayout from '../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';

const title = "Terminus Firefight Review - Halo Wars 2";
const description = "A comprehensive review of Terminus Firefight mode in Halo Wars 2. Discover the strategic depth, leader synergies, and what makes this mode worth playing.";
const category = "Reviews";
const publishedDate = "February 2, 2026";
const dateIso = "2026-02-02";
const tags = ["Halo Wars 2"];
const ogImage = "/content/blog/reviews-placeholder.svg";
---

<BlogPostLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  category={category}
  publishedDate={publishedDate}
  dateIso={dateIso}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  tags={tags}
  youtubeId="E0mbd03QuwY"
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    Terminus Firefight is included with the Awakening the Nightmare expansion pack or the Halo Wars 2 Complete Edition. It was one of the last pieces of content added to the game, and since the meta is stale, this review remains relevant.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300">The Good</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Different Strategic Layer</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Completely different team composition strategy than matchmaking</li>
    <li>Instead of thinking about destroying enemies or quick teleportation</li>
    <li>Focus on keeping the Terminus alive longer</li>
    <li>Terminus is in the center of the map with shields - game ends when its health depletes</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Great Leader Synergies</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Shipmaster's Displacement works well</li>
    <li>Johnson's Bunker Drops and Bunker Walls for garrisoning</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Siege excels</strong>: Anders' Siege and Pavium's Mega Turrets are excellent</li>
    <li>Johnson's Remote Sensors (expanded line of sight) helps Siege leaders flourish</li>
    <li>Can destroy many units before they reach the Terminus</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Variety and Twists</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Different enemies including the Flood on some waves</li>
    <li>Boss fights</li>
    <li>Flood waves</li>
    <li>Direct air attacks</li>
    <li>Keeps gameplay interesting</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Building Options</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Can build turrets and walls beyond initial base area</li>
    <li>Take mini bases for line of sight</li>
    <li>Direct enemies down particular paths</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Strategy</strong>: Wall off all entrances except one to create a funnel/choke point</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Relaxing Gameplay</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Less micromanaging than standard multiplayer</li>
    <li>Especially on economy side</li>
    <li>Can relax and let resources accumulate</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">The Bad</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Only One Map</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Same map over and over</li>
    <li>Main reason for not playing Terminus Firefight as much</li>
    <li>Same issue with Blitz Firefight (one map)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Wished-For Features</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Different map layouts</strong>: Full expansion bases (only minis available beyond starting base)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Flood-only mode</strong>: Like Flood Fight in MCC</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">PvPvE mode</strong>: Two Terminus objectives, each team defends while Flood attacks from center</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">New maps</strong>: Inspiration from multiplayer maps or callbacks to Halo Wars series (e.g., Arcadia City)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Limited Ranked Options</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Has ranked matchmaking</li>
    <li>Wished for more ranked variations like FPS Halo's Firefight options</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">No Mod Support</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Community could create map variations, unique challenges, or gameplay modifiers</li>
    <li>Examples: No siege, infantry only - to increase difficulty</li>
    <li>Would add significant replay value</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">What's Included</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">When you buy Awakening the Nightmare:</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Full Banished campaign (High Charity, Flood, blur cutscenes)</li>
    <li>Two new leaders (Voridus and Pavium)</li>
    <li>Terminus Firefight game mode</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Verdict</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Terminus Firefight is a great mode</strong> as an individual experience in Halo Wars 2. The issues don't make it bad - it's very fun and worth trying with friends if you have the Complete Edition or Awakening the Nightmare expansion.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    The single map repetition is the main drawback, but the strategic depth and relaxing gameplay make it an enjoyable change of pace from standard multiplayer.
  </p>

</BlogPostLayout>
